Boil a full #kettle{}.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a garlic press). Trim and thinly slice the @spring onion{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced).

Crush the @salted peanuts{25} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}.

Pour the boiled water from your kettle into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @jasmine rice{150} and cook for ~{10-12%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{}.

== Stir-Fry ==

While the rice cooks, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{120}, @diced British chicken breast{260}(diced), @sliced mushrooms{120}(sliced) and half the spring onion.

Stir-fry until golden, ~{5-6%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Once the chicken and bacon are golden and cooked through, add the garlic and @ginger puree{15}. Add the @hoisin sauce{32}, @ketjap manis{25} and @sambal paste{15} (add less if you'd prefer things milder).

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Stir-fry until fragrant, ~{1%min}.

== Finish ==

Once the rice is cooked, stir it into the bacon pan along with the @peas{120}, hoisin sauce, ketjap manis and sambal.

Mix well and stir-fry until piping hot, ~{1-2%mins}.

Taste and season with @salt and @ground black pepper if needed.

Share the bacon and chicken fried rice between your bowls.

Sprinkle over the peanuts and remaining spring onion to finish.

Enjoy!